<H3>Section 2.2: SPEED</H3>
<P>
<HR>
<FONT color=3Dfirebrick>Speed (Angular Velocity) </FONT>, as defined in =
=A9 1998=20
Merriam-Webster, Incorporated<BR><BR><CITE>Main Entry: angular=20
velocity<BR>Function: noun<BR>he rate of rotation around an axis usually =

expressed in radians or revolutions per second or per minute<BR></CITE>
<HR align=3Dleft width=3D"50%">
Motors are devices that convert electrical energy into mechanical =
energy. The=20
D.C. motors that we have been dealing with here convert electrical =
energy into=20
rotational energy. That rotational energy is then used to lift things, =
propel=20
things, turn things, etc... When we supply the specified voltage to a =
motor, it=20
rotates the output shaft at some speed. This <FONT =
color=3Dfirebrick>rotational=20
speed</FONT> or <FONT color=3Dfirebrick>angular velocity, <IMG alt=3DW =
src=3D""=20
align=3DTEXTBOTTOM></FONT> is typically measured in =
<STRONG>radians/second=20
{rad/s}, revolutions/second {rps}, or revolutions/minute {rpm}. =
</STRONG>
